CONCESSION STAND UPDATE from THE G-R FINE ARTS BOOSTER CLUB

The primary fundraiser for the Fine Arts Programs each year is running the Football Concession Stand. The money we raise directly benefits students in art, band, chorus, drama and speech.
Due to state restrictions, we are unable to provide a concession stand at this Friday's scrimmage. Fans will need to bring their own beverages and snacks. Schools can begin offering concession stands on Monday, August 24th.
Next week, we will be emailing the sign up link for this season's football games. We host the first high school football game next Friday against Meskwaki. We are reviewing the state's recommendations for concession stands and will be including some information in the email for our volunteers. We will still need our awesome volunteers to have a successful fundraising season for the Fine Arts Programs.

Thanks for your support.
The G-R Fine Arts Booster Club

GLADBROOK-REINBECK REGISTRATION ~ 08-11-20

Dear G-R Families: We hope you are all safe and well after the storm that ripped through our district yesterday. Many of our families are still without power and are cleaning up debris and repairing damage. We understand if you were not able to attend today's walk-in registration or were unable to register online. In light of these unfortunate events, the Gladbrook-Reinbeck registration deadline will be extended until MONDAY, August 17, 2020. The G-R Elementary and JH-HS Offices will be open until 3:30 PM that day for walk-in questions.

If you have any questions or concerns, please reach out to your student(s) Building Office or contact the G-R Superintendent's Office at the numbers listed below:
G-R JH-HS = (319) 345-2921
G-R Elementary = (319) 345-2822
G-R Superintendent's Office = (319) 345-2712

GLADBROOK-REINBECK FINAL VIRTUAL LEARNING COUNT-FILL OUT BY 08-14-20

If you are choosing Virtual Instruction for the first Trimester please fill out this G-R VIRTUAL LEARNING COUNT FORM. If you are choosing in-person instruction please disregard this form.

- THIS IS THROUGH THE SCHOOL AND RECEIVING INSTRUCTION FROM G-R TEACHERS.

post_text:
GLADBROOK-REINBECK HS PROM DINNER & WALK-IN ~ 07-16-20

Gladbrook-Reinbeck After-Prom will be hosting G-R Juniors and Seniors for a Prom Walk-In and Formal Dinner on Thursday, 07-16-20.

The car parade and walk-in will be held at Elmwood Park in Reinbeck. Walk-In and introduction of students begins at 5:30 PM. Students will exit their cars at the sidewalk entrance on College Street and promenade toward the shelter building, where they will be announced. A parent or family member of the student will drive the vehicle from College Street to the horseshoe parking lot so the couples can proceed to PT Grillers for the formal dinner, which begins at 6:00 PM.

Those who wish to view the walk-in may park in the north end of the gravel horseshoe parking lot, at the pool parking lot or along College Street.

Social distancing and masks are welcome.

post_text:
CANCELLATION OF THE 2020 IOWA SHRINE BOWL

The 48th annual Iowa Shrine Bowl was set for Saturday, July 18, 2020. We are very proud that our very own Gladbrook-Reinbeck Senior, Aidan Walters, was selected as one of the 42 athletes to participate in the North vs South All-Star Game. Due to the events over the past few months we regret to inform all of REBEL NATION that the game has been cancelled for the summer of 2020.

The Iowa Shrine Bowl Board of Directors met recently and made this very difficult decision. They evaluated the size of the event, and with the social distancing guidelines, they did not feel it would be safe to host this year's football camp, game, parade, or banquet. This is disappointing to all of the game's participants and everyone associated with the Iowa Shrine Bowl. We are very appreciative of those individuals, groups, and businesses who donated, as all money will benefit those in need at the Shriners Hospital for Children.

Congratulations to Aidan Walters for a tremendous senior season for the Rebels and an outstanding career at Gladbrook-Reinbeck.

post_text:
G-R SUMMER ACTIVITIES ANNOUNCEMENT

Gladbrook-Reinbeck Rebels ~ as you know Governor Reynolds announced Wednesday [05-20-20] that Athletics may resume on June 1, 2020. Then as of Thursday [05-21-20] we received more guidance from the Department of Education in coordination with IHSAA/IGHSAU in regards to summer activities.

The following are some of the main points detailed:
* HS Baseball/Softball Practices may begin June 1st
* HS Baseball/Softball Games may begin June 15th
* No JH Baseball/Softball Practices or Games
* 8th graders are allowed to play HS baseball/softball based on local rules
* All other sports and activities are suspended until further notice
* JH/HS Weight Room is closed until further notice

We realize you may have many more questions, but at this time we are all working to find answers as we wait for guidance from the State Athletic Associations. We will send out additional details to our Rebel Nation athletes, parents and fans as they become known to us. Thank you for your patience during these difficult times.

post_text:
May is School Board Recognition Month in Iowa. Gladbrook-Reinbeck’s School Board Members are Matt Wyatt (President), Doug Rowe (Vice President), Lisa Swanson, Rod Brockett, Susie Petersen, Christine Farley, and Donovan Devore.

School board members invest countless hours preparing for and attending board meetings, committee meetings, and training opportunities. They also spend hours studying documents and financial information, asking & answering questions, developing and reviewing policies, and setting the direction for the school’s long-term vision. They are unpaid volunteers who dedicate their time, talents, and expertise to create the conditions that will allow every child in the Gladbrook-Reinbeck Community School District to receive a quality public education.

On behalf of the students, staff, and school community – THANK YOU to our board members for their loyalty, commitment, and vision for Gladbrook-Reinbeck Schools!

GLADBROOK-REINBECK KINDERGARTEN ROUND-UP ANNOUNCEMENT ~ 04-29-20

Hello Gladbrook-Reinbeck Families,
We are hard at work planning for our upcoming kindergarten class for the fall of 2020. With the closing of the building we won't be holding a traditional kindergarten round up. Instead we are working on a plan for kindergarten round up in August.

In the next week, we'll be mailing the kindergarten packets that we usually give out at the parent meeting. We'll mail these out to families we have in our school information system. If you know of any other families with students who will be attending kindergarten in the fall, please contact the school at 319-345-2822 and we'll get information sent out. As a reminder, students eligible for kindergarten must be five years old by September 15, 2020.

Thank you, Mrs. J.

post_text:
G-R Families:

Yesterday, April 2, 2020, Governor Reynolds announced that Iowa's Public Schools will remain closed until April 30, 2020. We also received guidance for moving ahead with distance learning, and Gladbrook-Reinbeck is working on a plan to get this started the week of April 13, 2020 for Grades K-12. Continued learning is very important for our students and we expect all of our students to participate in G-R's distance learning opportunities. Our staff and teachers are working on a plan to support families and students as we transition to distance learning.

Please know we understand these are trying times, however, we look forward to working together with you to do all we can to promote learning for your students. Now more than ever we are here for you and your children. Together, we will learn, discover, be flexible, and problem solve through this transition.

Most importantly, we look forward to the opportunity to connect with you and your children. We are G-R!

post_text:
The school is working through the application process to provide lunches as other districts are doing. "Feed The Rebels" is a group of concerned individuals who are stepping in to fill the gap for all of our students “in the meantime” until we know if/when Gladbrook-Reinbeck will qualify for the shutdown meals. The "Feed the Rebels" group is willing to deliver to Gladbrook, Lincoln, Morrison, Reinbeck, etc. Please contact them for more information.
Thank you everyone for your help and cooperation!
Rebel Nation is an amazing community!
shared_text:
Karyn Morgan‎Feed the Rebels 💙
March 20 at 6:38 PM ·

We have a plan.

We have a menu planned for Monday-Friday next week.

Our pick up location will be the United Church of Christ from 11-12:30 every week day. Just pull up and tell us how many lunches you need. IF possible please let us know you are coming so we can be prepared.

We have an account set up at Truncks called "Feed the Rebels" if you would like to donate money. Just tell them you want to put a credit on the account. We will be getting ALL of our supplies from them. Support Local!!

If you have any questions/helpful suggestions please let us know.

Please share this group so we can get the word out to everyone who may benefit.

Also delivery may also be an option. If this would benefit you please let us know. We want to help out as many Rebels as we can!

The Iowa Youth Fishing League is a not for profit with the mission to support youth fishing among Iowans through educational programs, mentoring and competition, so that Iowa youth develop leadership skills and become stewards of our natural resources. Anglers that wish to tournament fish must be ages 7-18. Angler registration is now open to all who are interested.
Please see the attached our flyer, or go to the IYFL website for details.

SCHOLASTIC BOOK FAIR at GLADBROOK-REINBECK ELEMENTARY
Conferences are coming, which means the Scholastic Book Fair is coming, too! Stop by G-R Elementary next week and support our school libraries.

Shopping Days
The fair will be open for business when conferences start on Monday, March 9. The fair will also be open before and after school March 10, 11, and 12. The fair will be packed up on Thursday, March 12.

Online Shopping
Can't make it to the fair? Online shopping starts on Wednesday, March 4 and is open until March 17! Profits gained from online shopping will still benefit our school and the products get delivered straight to the buyer - they will not be delivered to school. Access the online shopping website here:https://bookfairs.scholastic.com/…/gladbrookreinbeckelemsch…

Proceeds gained during the book fair will be used to add new and exciting titles into our elementary and secondary library collections.

If you have any questions, please reach out to Mrs. Biederman at emily.biederman@gr-rebels.net.

48th ANNUAL IOWA SHRINE BOWL ~ 07-18-20

Gladbrook-Reinbeck is pleased to announce that G-R Senior Football Player, Aidan Walters, was one of 42 athletes invited to participate in the 48th Annual Iowa Shrine Bowl. In addition, G-R's very own Coach John Olson was selected as one of the Shrine Bowl Assistant Coaches!

This year the Shrine Bowl will be played at the Cedar Falls UNI-Dome on Saturday, 07-18-20.

Tickets are $11.00 in advance, or $15.00 at the gate.

Please see Coach Olson or Aidan Walters for pre-sale tickets.

Finishing in the Top 100: Jace Petersen (8th), Chloe Schipper (11th), Henry Mussig (29th), Reid Ehmen (43rd), Kaleb Brouwer (50th), Bell Rogers (59th) and Ella Schipper (80th). There were over 250 kids who judged in the individual contest.
Out of 60 teams, Jace Petersen, Kaleb Brouwer, Brady Feckers and Reid Ehmen placed 7th.

CONGRATULATIONS on your stellar results!

GLADBROOK-REINBECK THIRD GRADE FARM CHAT

The G-R Third Grade Teachers organize a monthly farm chat where farmers Skype into the classroom and talk to the kids about what they are doing.
Our farm chat this month took us to Hansen Dairy Farm. It was fun to see the calves, cows as well as the kangaroos. We learned that they milk 150 cows twice a day and get 1200 gallons of milk per day!

FREE-REDUCED PRICE SCHOOL MEAL PROGRAM

Dear Gladbrook-Reinbeck CSD Parents and Guardians:
Children need healthy meals to learn. GLADBROOK-REINBECK CSD offers healthy meals every school day. Breakfast cost $2.10; lunch costs $2.85 [for Grades K-4] and $3.10 [for Grades 5-12]. Your children may qualify for free meals/milk or for reduced price meals. Reduced price is $0.30 [for all Grades] for breakfast and $0.40 [for all Grades] for lunch.

Please note that if you have already applied and been granted free or reduced cost lunch status, you DO NOT NEED TO REAPPLY. No further action is necessary to continue meal benefits for those already approved for free or reduced price meals in the current year.

If you would like to apply for free or reduced price meal benefits, please contact the Superintendent's Office to have an application mailed to you. Return the completed application to: Gladbrook-Reinbeck CSD, Superintendent's Office, 600 Blackhawk Street, Reinbeck, Iowa 50669; Tel: (319) 345-2712.

GLADBROOK-REINBECK HIGH SCHOOL ~ HEALTH CLASS

Friday before Winter Break, the G-R Health Class students participated in a relay using the Fatal Vision Goggles to experience what it might be like to walk while impaired.

We needed one more person to make our relay teams even, and we'd like to thank our very own Ms. Seidl for filling that need!

The students quickly came to a conclusion that nobody should drive while impaired.

shared_text:
Kathy Roman-Etringer is with Janean Walvoord Skovgard and 2 others.
December 18, 2019 at 10:22 PM ·

Mrs. Rowe came up with the best project for her FCS class to do with my kindergarten class! I had each child in my class draw an elf and we spent about a week writing a story to go with each one of the elves. Without my kid's knowledge I sent their elf pictures over to Mrs Rowe. She had her class sew elves to match the pictures that my kids drew. My kids had no idea that the high school kids were making these elves. Today Mrs. Rowe's class surprised my class with their stuffed elves and my kids read their stories to their high school friends!

NICL VOCAL MUSIC MEAL - HELP NEEDED

On Tuesday, January 21, 2020, the Gladbrook-Reinbeck Vocal Department is hosting an NICL Vocal Concert at 7:00 PM. The students from Denver, Jesup, and Union will arrive in the early afternoon and practice with our GR students in preparation for the 7:00 PM performance.

The GR Fine Arts Boosters will be preparing and serving a meal for the students. Any Fine Arts parents who would like to be involved in the planning of the meal, please call or text Rod Brockett at 515-341-1327 or email Rod at rod.brockett@gr-rebels.net by next Tuesday, December 17, 2019. Another email will be sent in early January with a sign-up for volunteers to help serve the meal and/or donate a dessert.

Thanks for your support of GR Fine Arts!

GLADBROOK-REINBECK COMMUNITY ANNOUNCEMENTS ~ 12-06-19

KDAO VIDIO BROADCAST ~ 12-06-19

Watch High School Basketball tonight from State Center. West Marshall will host Gladbrook-Reinbeck in an NICL Western Division clash. Andy Jennings will have the call, pregame is at 6:07 PM. Girls tip off at 6:15 PM, followed by the Boys' game. Click on the following link to listen online: http://kdao.com/high-school-basketball-west-marshall-vs-gr-december-6th-607-p-m/

FFA AGRICULTURE APPRECIATION PANCAKE BREAKFAST ~ 12-07-19

It's been a long harvest season! The T-55 FFA Members want to show their appreciation to those who have been working incredibly hard this Fall. Farmers, Co-Op employees, and all agricultural workers involved in our local harvest are welcome to join us for a pancake breakfast on December 7, 2019. It will be held from 7:00-10:00 AM at Dike-New Hartford High School. Enjoy a delicious breakfast and learn more about our program, while we celebrate your hard work. Contact Mr. Hunter Hamilton at hunter.hamilton@gr-rebels.net for more info! See attached flyer for details.

post_text:
SCHOLASTIC BOOK FAIR AT GLADBROOK-REINBECK ELEMENTARY ~ 11-18-19 through 11-22-19

Come support our school libraries by attending our Scholastic Book Fair at the elementary!
The book fair opens for sales starting on Monday, 11-18-19 at 2:00 pm during elementary conferences until 8:00 pm. It will be open the rest of the week, before and after school from 7:30-8:15 AM and 3:15-4:00 PM. Proceeds gained during the book fair will be used to add new and exciting titles into our elementary and secondary library collections.

Can't make it to the fair? You can shop online starting Wednesday, November 13 for two weeks, even after the fair leaves the school! Online shopping dates are open from 11/13 - 11/26 using this link: https://bookfairs.scholastic.com/bookfairs/cptoolkit/homepage.do?method=homepage&url=gladbrookreinbeckelemschool1

While you're there, check out our library wish list!

post_text:
THE REBEL WAY
Last week, on Wednesday, October 23, GLADBROOK-REINBECK ELEMENTARY had a chance to practice the Rebel Way!
Coach Charley and the 6th grade students were POSITIVE ROLE MODELS and guided students together to learn new games to play with their classmates, we were reminded of the appropriate way to play some old favorites, and learned new ways to use equipment. They practiced TEAMWORK when learning together, showed RESPECT to their Rebel Buddies and the 6th graders, and had to be RESPONSIBLE to learn and remember the games.
What a GReat morning to be a Rebel!

post_text:
School Election Day is just one week from today! (Tuesday, November 5)

Not registered to vote? No problem! Just bring proof of ID and proof of residence and you can register at the polls! Polls will be open from 7 a.m. to 8 p.m. on Tuesday, November 5.

Not sure where to vote? (Note: Polling places have changed for many voters since the last school election) Just visit https://tinyurl.com/FindPolls and enter your address to locate your polling place.

For more information on Public Measure E (also known as the Revenue Purpose Statement) visit https://tinyurl.com/RPSQandA.

Note:
*The G-R School Board has passed a resolution encouraging voters to vote YES on Public Measure E.
*A prevailing YES vote will NOT increase any tax but will give the Board of Education flexibility to use state sales tax revenues in the broadest ways permitted by law.
